# <type>: <subject>
#
# Types:
#   feat     New feature
#   fix      Bug fix
#   docs     Documentation only
#   style    Formatting, whitespace (no code change)
#   refactor Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#   perf     Performance improvement
#   test     Adding or fixing tests
#   chore    Build, deps, config, CI (no production code change)
#
# Subject: imperative, ≤50 chars, lowercase, no period.
#
# Examples:
#   feat: add prior tax paid input to ETF rows
#   fix: handle timezone-naive datetimes in deemed disposal
#   docs: add web app quick start to user guide
#   refactor: extract etf exit tax into per-ticker function
#   test: add integration test for deemed disposal year attribution
#
# ---
#
# If needed, add a body explaining what and why (wrap at 72 chars).
# Use bullet points for multiple changes.
#
#   More detailed explanation of the change. Wrap lines at 72
#   characters. Break logically between paragraphs.
#
#   - Bullet points are okay
#   - Use present tense ("add" not "added")
#   - Use imperative mood ("fix" not "fixed")
#
# ---
#
# Footer for breaking changes or issue references:
#
#   BREAKING CHANGE: description of what broke
#   Closes #123, #456
#   Related to #789
#
